projects.name: Libraro
projects.description: Designed and implemented a library management system using React.js for the frontend and Express.js, Node.js, and MySQL for the backend.Distinct roles: administrators can add new books, and users can search for books with filter options This project includes database management, user authentication, and role-based access control.

projects.name: Dlvery-App
projects.description: Developed a delivery app with inventory management, delivery coordination, and customer interaction. Inventory managers add and track products with real-time updates, the delivery team has automated order assignment and optimized routes, and customers can book products, track orders, and provide feedback.. This project showcases expertise in creating efficient, real-time logistics solutions and enhancing operational efficiency through automation and optimized processes.

projects.name: ErrorEx
projects.description: Developed a Coders-Community project where users post coding errors with screenshots stored in a MySQL database. Admins and developers can view these images and provide solutions via Nodemailer, streamlining error resolution and enhancing coder collaboration. This project highlights the ability to integrate database management and email communication to facilitate community-driven problem-solving and collaboration.

projects.name: House Rental
projects.description: Developed "HouseRent," a comprehensive platform designed for seamless property rentals. The application includes secure login and signup features for property owners and renters, allowing owners to list their houses with detailed descriptions and images. Users can search for rental properties based on various criteria such as rental amount, number of rooms, and location. The platform also features a booking system enabling users to rent houses directly. With a responsive design, HouseRent ensures a smooth user experience across different devices.
